Long way to go before enacting bank reform - Rubin . U . S . Treasury Secretary Robert Rubin said on Saturday that Congress has a long way to go before approving an overhaul of America ' s outdated banking laws and suggested that passage may not come until next year . " We ' ve got a lot to do on this , " Rubin told reporters here for the annual summit of industrial nations . " banking bills , as you know , are always very difficutl to get . " Congress on Friday moved one step closer to tearing down the Depression - era barriers separating banking from other financial services , as the House Banking Committee narrowly approved a comprehensive reform bill . 
